"title": "8728: enemies, of Israel and Judah",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8728: enemies, of israel and judah",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Throughout their history, Israel and Judah contended with enemies committed to their destruction, finding refuge only in their covenant-keeping God.</p>\n<h2>Enemies of Israel</h2>\n<h3>The Egyptians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:8-Exod1:11\">EXO 1:8–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:9\">EXO 14:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:25\">1KI 14:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:2\">2CH 12:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:3\">2CH 36:3</a></p>\n<h3>The Amalekites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:8\">EXO 17:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:13\">JDG 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>The Edomites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:18\">NUM 20:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:14\">1KI 11:14</a></p>\n<h3>Sihon, king of the Amorites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:23\">NUM 21:23</a></p>\n<h3>Og, king of Bashan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:33\">NUM 21:33</a></p>\n<h3>The Canaanites and the surrounding nations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:1-Josh11:5\">JOS 11:1–11:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Syrians (Arameans)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:8\">JDG 3:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:25\">1KI 11:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:1\">1KI 20:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:8\">2KI 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:24\">2KI 6:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:2\">2KI 24:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:5\">2CH 28:5</a></p>\n<h3>The Moabites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:12\">JDG 3:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:1\">2KI 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:2\">2KI 24:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Ammonites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:13\">JDG 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:9\">JDG 10:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6\">1CH 19:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:2\">2KI 24:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Midianites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:1\">JDG 6:1</a></p>\n<h3>The Philistines</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:7-Judg10:8\">JDG 10:7–10:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:1-1Sam4:2\">1SA 4:1–4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:1-1Sam17:2\">1SA 17:1–17:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:1\">1SA 31:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:17\">2SA 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1\">2SA 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:15\">2SA 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:18\">2SA 21:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:4\">1CH 20:4</a></p>\n<h3>The Assyrians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:19\">2KI 15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:29\">2KI 15:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:3-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:3–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:13\">2KI 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>The Babylonians</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:1\">2KI 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:1\">2KI 25:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:5-2Chr36:7\">2CH 36:5–36:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15-2Chr36:20\">2CH 36:15–36:20</a></p>\n<h3>Those opposed to the rebuilding under Ezra and Nehemiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:4-Ezra4:6\">EZR 4:4–4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:3\">EZR 5:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:10\">NEH 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Haman the Persian</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:5-Esth3:6\">EST 3:5–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>The Greeks</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:13\">ZEC 9:13</a></p>\n<h3>The Romans</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:48\">JHN 11:48</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of Israel's enemies</h2>\n<h3>They were often more numerous than Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:5\">1SA 13:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:12\">NAM 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>They were often better equipped</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:16\">JOS 17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:19-1Sam13:22\">1SA 13:19–13:22</a></p>\n<h3>They were cruel and oppressive</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:23\">JER 6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:5-Exod6:9\">EXO 6:5–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:33\">DEU 28:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:2-Judg6:6\">JDG 6:2–6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:42\">JER 50:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:6\">HAB 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>They were cunning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:3\">PSA 83:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They were determined to destroy Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:4\">PSA 83:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They were often in league with each other</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:5-Ps83:8\">PSA 83:5–83:8</a></p>\n<h2>God helped Israel against her enemies</h2>\n<h3>He opposed Israel's enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:3\">GEN 12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:22\">EXO 23:22</a></p>\n<h3>He protected Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:14\">DEU 23:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:15\">NEH 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:16\">NEH 6:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:2\">PSA 125:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:22\">ISA 51:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:19\">ISA 59:19</a></p>\n<h3>He delivered Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:9\">NUM 10:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:11\">1SA 12:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:39\">2KI 17:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:71\">LUK 1:71</a></p>\n<h3>He gave Israel victory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:27\">EXO 23:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:7-Lev26:8\">LEV 26:7–26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:35\">NUM 10:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:19\">DEU 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:12\">PSA 60:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:13\">PSA 108:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:1\">PSA 68:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:15\">ISA 54:15</a></p>\n<h3>He destroyed Israel's enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:6\">EXO 15:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:17\">DEU 20:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:7\">DEU 30:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:19\">JOS 10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:29\">2CH 20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:5\">PSA 44:5</a></p>\n<h3>He gave Israel rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:10\">DEU 12:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:19\">DEU 25:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:3-1Kgs5:4\">1KI 5:3–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:9\">1CH 22:9</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's attitude towards her enemies</h2>\n<h3>Israel was not to fear them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:1-Deut20:4\">DEU 20:1–20:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:45-1Sam17:47\">1SA 17:45–17:47</a></p>\n<h3>Israel was to pray for deliverance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:33-1Kgs8:34\">1KI 8:33–8:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:24-2Chr6:25\">2CH 6:24–6:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:37-1Kgs8:40\">1KI 8:37–8:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:28-2Chr6:31\">2CH 6:28–6:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:22-Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:22–8:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:3\">PSA 74:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:10\">PSA 74:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:18\">PSA 74:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:22-Ps74:23\">PSA 74:22–74:23</a></p>\n<h3>Kindness was to be shown to Israel's enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:4-Exod23:5\">EXO 23:4–23:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:21-2Kgs6:23\">2KI 6:21–6:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:21-Prov25:22\">PRO 25:21–25:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:20\">ROM 12:20</a></p>\n<h2>Thanksgiving for victory over Israel's enemies</h2>\n<h3>Giving thanks to God was the proper response to victory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1\">EXO 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:11-2Sam8:12\">2SA 8:11–8:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:11\">1CH 18:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:24\">PSA 136:24</a></p>\n<h3>Israel often forgot to give thanks to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:33-Judg8:34\">JDG 8:33–8:34</a></p>\n<h2>God used enemies to chastise Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:47-Deut28:48\">DEU 28:47–28:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:44\">LEV 26:44</a> <em>Because of his covenant, the LORD was unwilling to destroy Israel completely at the hand of her enemies</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:53\">DEU 28:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:10-Judg2:23\">JDG 2:10–2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:1\">JDG 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:5-Isa8:8\">ISA 8:5–8:8</a></p>",
